# Git remote and push policy

This project lives at `https://github.com/BethelHills/aeroroute-ai.git`.

After completing meaningful work in this repo:

1. Stage all relevant changes (`git add -A` from the project root).
2. Commit with a clear message describing why the change was made.
3. Push to `origin main` (`git push -u origin main` if upstream is not set).

Do not push unrelated files from outside this project directory. Keep commits scoped to `/Users/hb/aeroroute-ai`.

If the user asks to push or says work is done, commit and push without waiting for a separate commit request.
